# ChroPlexiGnosis Design Guidelines

## Color Scheme
Always use the defined color constants from [lib/core/constants/colors.dart](mdc:lib/core/constants/colors.dart):

- **Primary Dark**: Deep space blue (#0A192F) - Main background color
- **Primary Accent**: Cyber cyan (#00F5D4) - Buttons, icons, and key UI elements
- **Secondary Accent**: Neon pink (#FF00F7) - Special features and highlights
- **Text Color**: Soft white (#E6F1FF) - For readable text on dark backgrounds

## Visual Style
- Use glassmorphic effects for UI containers (semi-transparent backgrounds with blur)
- Apply glow effects to interactive elements using the primary or secondary accent colors
- Use hexagon shapes for level selection and special game elements
- Implement subtle animations for transitions and feedback
- Maintain a cyberpunk aesthetic throughout all screens

## Typography
- Use the system font for all text
- Apply consistent text sizing hierarchy:
  - Screen titles: 24-32sp
  - Section headers: 18-22sp
  - Body text: 14-16sp
  - Small labels: 12sp

## UI Components
- Buttons should have rounded corners (borderRadius: 16-24)
- Cards should use the glassmorphic effect with subtle borders
- Game board should maintain an 8x8 grid with appropriate spacing
- Navigation elements should be intuitive and consistent across screens